				\begin{document}$$Y=Y{\rm{\Gamma }}+X{\rm{\Psi }}+{\rm{{\rm E}}},$$\end{document}Y=YΓ+XΨ+Ε,where the p × p matrix Γ has zero diagonal elements and contains gene regulatory effects, the q × q matrix Ψ contains causal genomic effects from cis-eQTL, and E is an n × p matrix of error terms. We assume that X and E are independent of each other, and each component of E is independently distributed as normal with zero mean while its rows are identically distributed.
